deck: Biography of the comic creator Daniel Govar, Writer/Artist of the comic Azure for Zudacomics. His history as an illustrator and concept artist and background as a Creative Director for a media firm are detailed.
description:
Daniel Govar is an artist who works in pencil, watercolor, and digitally. For Azure, his most recent work, Govar creates everything digitally. For the book "The Highwayman" by R.A. Salvatore, Govar adapted the first chapter into a 12 page comic for the novel's launch.  
 
He has also illustrated dozens of book covers, has a background in concept art,  and his artwork has graced media of all formats.  Govar also created the award winning Tolkien website ThereAndBackAgain.net;  dedicated to visualizing the world created by J.R.R. Tolkien. It has garnered numerous awards and has been featured in publications such as Entertainment Weekly and TV Guide. When not creating comics and illustrations he is the creative director at a media firm outside of Washington  D.C.
name: Daniel Govar

description:
Career

A freelance artist and occasional writer, Johnnie Christmas has produced work that can be seen in Cloudscape Anthologies: Exploded View, 21 Journeys and Murder Book. He has done varied freelance work, working for Devil's Due and ShadowLine among others. He is currently working on his webcomic Spectre of Sound, and has work in the upcoming anthology Giants on Main Street. He is also working on the Continuum graphic novel.

Personal Life

Christmas currently lives in Vancouver.
name: John Christmas

description:
Phibbz was formerly working as an animator at the Philippine studios of Japanese anime company, Toei Animation, on cartoons such as Digimon, Beet the Vandel Buster, One Piece and Pretty Cure Splash Star.

He first dreamed of working in comics as a kid after having read The Flash, Firestorm, Spiderman, and Justice League of America.

Other books to his credit include the webcomic "The Celestial" and the Kickstarter-funded "Zombie Plague" oneshot.

deck: Jason Starr is a bestselling thriller and and horror writer known for his original graphic novel The Chill.
description: Jason Starr was born in 1966 in Brooklyn, New York. He first began writing with mostly crime novels while at Birmingham University. In 2010, Jason Starr wrote The Chill for Vertigo Crime. The Chill was the very first graphic novel to win the Anthony award for a graphic novel. His other work in comics include Doc Savage and Untold Tales of the Punisher Max. Starting in late 2012, Starr will be writing the Wolverine MAX ongoing series with covers by jock.
name: Jason Starr
